The World Series begins tonight, and whatever happens on the field will be instant history. But let's not forget baseball's most infamous moment, as called by Yankee announcer Phil Rizzuto.
The outlook wasn't brilliant for the Mudville nine that day;
The score stood four to two, with but one inning more to play;
Hey Murcer! Who's got play-by-play? No? Really? I do?
Those last two outs I been sitting here, thinking it was you.
